@startuml
' ============================================================
' Diagram   : Hypervisor Clustering - Heartbeat and Failover
' Section   : 14.1 Hypervisor Clustering Architecture
' Type      : Sequence diagram
' Message   : VIM-orchestrated live VM migration restores hosted
'             virtual servers when a hypervisor stops responding.
' ============================================================

!include ../../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/interaction/sequence-diagram-style.iuml

title 14.1 Hypervisor Clustering\nHeartbeat and Failover Sequence

skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam ActorBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam DatabaseBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam DatabaseBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF8DC
skinparam noteBorderColor #999999

actor "Cloud Resource\nAdministrator" as Admin
participant "VIM" as VIM
participant "Hypervisor A\n(Physical Server A)" as HA
participant "Hypervisor B\n(Physical Server B)" as HB
participant "Hypervisor C\n(Physical Server C)" as HC
database "Shared Cloud\nStorage Device" as STG

== Cluster setup ==
Admin -> VIM : enable hypervisor cluster
VIM -> HA : install / join cluster
VIM -> HB : install / join cluster
VIM -> HC : install / join cluster
HA -> STG : access VM\nconfig files
HB -> STG : access VM\nconfig files
HC -> STG : access VM\nconfig files

== Scheduled heartbeats ==
loop predefined schedule
  HA -> VIM : heartbeat
  HB -> VIM : heartbeat
  HC -> VIM : heartbeat
end

== Hypervisor failure ==
note over HB #FFE0E0
  Physical Server B fails;
  Virtual Server C is jeopardized
end note
HB -x VIM : heartbeat\nstops
VIM -> VIM : assess available\ncapacity in cluster

== Live VM migration ==
VIM -> HC : assign Virtual Server C
HC -> STG : read Virtual\nServer C config
HC -> HC : start Virtual Server C\n(restart if needed)
HC --> VIM : migration complete

note over VIM, HC
  Mechanisms: hypervisor, resource cluster, virtual server,
  logical network perimeter, resource replication.
end note

@enduml

